This is a TypeScript cli repository using Next.js.

When creating or renaming files, follow: kebab-case for most files (e.g. `agents-md.ts`, `subagent-writer.ts`, `cost.ts`); test files colocated as `*.test.ts` or under `__tests__/` subdirectories; `.js` extensions used in all import paths within `packages/core/src/`
When building React components, follow: PascalCase React components (e.g. `AuthProvider`, `Generator`, `PhaseSpinner`); shadcn-ui components under `packages/web/components/ui/`
When naming functions and hooks, follow: camelCase for all functions and async generators (e.g. `runAgent`, `renderFormats`, `deriveProjectCommands`, `buildAgentsJsonManifest`); `run*` prefix for top-level CLI command handlers
When naming variables and constants, follow: camelCase throughout; `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` for module-level constants (e.g. `ALL_FORMAT_IDS`, `MAX_FILE_BYTES`, `SUBAGENT_GENERATION_SYSTEM`)

When organizing modules and directories, follow this layout: Monorepo with three packages under `packages/`: `core` (all LLM pipeline logic, adapters, providers, types), `cli` (Commander-based CLI with `src/commands/`, `src/ui/`, `src/config.ts`, `src/target.ts`), and `web` (Next.js app with `app/`, `components/`, `lib/`). Core exports everything through `packages/core/src/index.ts` and is consumed by both CLI and web via `@skillsmith/core`. Tests in `packages/core/src/__tests__/` mirror the source subdirectory structure, with shared fixtures in `__tests__/fixtures/` and helpers in `__tests__/load-fixture.ts`.

When handling errors and API failures, follow: CLI command handlers wrap all async work in try/catch, print `chalk.red(e.message)` to stderr, and call `process.exit(2)` for operational errors or `process.exit(1)` for user errors (e.g. missing API key). Custom error classes like `AgentsJsonParseError` are used for typed catches in both CLI and core; `instanceof` checks gate specific recovery paths before re-throwing unknown errors.
When managing client or server state, follow: No client-side state management library; Next.js server components and next-auth session context (via `AuthProvider`) handle web state. CLI commands are stateless imperative flows; pipeline state is passed explicitly through function arguments and async generator yields (`AgentProgressEvent`).
When adding or changing tests, follow: Vitest with `describe`/`it`/`expect` in all packages; provider tests use `vi.hoisted` + `vi.mock` to intercept SDK constructors before imports, and `vi.stubGlobal('fetch', ...)` for Ollama. Adapter render tests use `toMatchSnapshot()` against fixtures loaded via `loadSampleConventions()` from `packages/core/src/__tests__/load-fixture.ts`. File-system integration tests create temp dirs under `packages/core/.vitest-tmp/` and clean up in `finally` blocks. Run tests with `pnpm test` (no test script is defined at root; tests are run per-package).

Prefer these libraries when they already solve the problem: next, next-auth, @anthropic-ai/sdk, openai, commander, tailwindcss, shadcn-ui, zod, vitest.
Use pnpm for installs and scripts.

When working near or extending "Adapter interface" (packages/core/src/adapters/registry.ts), Uniform `{ format, filename, render(conv, provider?) }` contract for all output format renderers; registered in a central Map and iterated in `renderFormats`

When working near or extending "LLMProvider interface" (packages/core/src/types.ts), Abstraction over Anthropic, OpenAI, and Ollama SDKs exposing `generate({ system, user, maxTokens, temperature, expectJson })` and `estimateCostUsd`; created via `createProvider` / `createProviderFromEnv`

When working near or extending "runAgent async generator" (packages/core/src/index.ts), Top-level pipeline entry point yielding `AgentProgressEvent` objects through inventory → sample → extract → reduce → subagents phases; callers iterate with `for await`

When working near or extending "SubagentDefinition + compile targets" (packages/core/src/adapters/subagentAdapters.js), Typed spec for Claude Code / Cursor subagents; `compileClaudeCodeSubagent` and `compileCursorSubagent` render to `.md` / `.mdc`; `writeSubagentsForCompileTarget` handles file I/O per target

When working near or extending "mergeGenerateConfig" (packages/cli/src/config.ts), Merges CLI flags > env vars > `~/.skillsmith/config.json` > defaults into a single `MergedGenerateConfig` object consumed by `runGenerate`

When working near or extending "loadSampleConventions fixture helper" (packages/core/src/__tests__/load-fixture.ts), Loads `fixtures/sample-conventions.json` as a typed `Conventions` object for use across all adapter snapshot tests

When working near or extending "cn utility" (packages/web/lib/utils.ts), Combines `clsx` + `tailwind-merge` for conditional Tailwind class composition in all web components

When working near or extending "FormatId / FORMAT_META" (packages/cli/src/util.ts), Const-asserted union type and metadata record for the four supported output format IDs; used for CLI validation, display labels, and format detection mapping

Do not do the following:
- Don't add import paths without the `.js` extension inside `packages/core/src/` — all internal imports use explicit `.js` suffixes for ESM compatibility even though source files are `.ts`
- Don't invent new adapter formats outside the `Adapter` interface and `adapterRegistry` in `packages/core/src/adapters/registry.ts` — all formats must be registered there to be reachable by `renderFormats`
- Don't call `process.exit` from inside `packages/core/` — exit calls belong only in CLI command handlers in `packages/cli/src/commands/`
- Don't skip the `AgentsJsonParseError` instanceof check when calling `parseAgentsJsonFromText` — unknown errors must be re-thrown, not swallowed
- Don't write subagent temp files to `os.tmpdir()` in tests — use the workspace-local `.vitest-tmp/` directory under `packages/core/` to avoid sandbox permission issues
- Don't bypass `mergeGenerateConfig` to read config or env vars directly in command handlers — all flag/env/file merging must go through that function
- Don't pass `low` confidence `TaskPattern` entries to `generateSubagents` — only `high` and `medium` confidence patterns should trigger LLM calls
- Don't add direct Anthropic/OpenAI/Ollama SDK calls outside `packages/core/src/providers/` — all LLM access must go through the `LLMProvider` interface

For the recurring task "Add a new output adapter format", follow this procedure exactly:
1. Create `packages/core/src/adapters/<format-name>.ts` exporting a `render(conv: Conventions): string` function and an `Adapter` object with `format`, `filename`, and async `render` wrapping the sync function.
2. Export both from `packages/core/src/index.ts`.
3. Register the adapter in `packages/core/src/adapters/registry.ts` by adding it to the `adapters` record keyed by its `format` string.
4. Add the format ID to `ALL_FORMAT_IDS` in `packages/cli/src/util.ts` and add its entry to `FORMAT_META` with `label`, `tool`, and `example` fields.
5. Add a snapshot test in `packages/core/src/__tests__/adapters/<format-name>.test.ts` using `loadSampleConventions()` and `toMatchSnapshot()`.
6. Run tests with `pnpm test` inside `packages/core` to generate the snapshot and confirm no regressions.